The paper focuses on learning robotic manipulation tasks using reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of graph-based relational architectures and their ability to transfer knowledge from simpler to complex tasks suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of simulations and the demonstration of the method on a block stacking task suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
